'''Irreligion in Rwanda''' is uncommon among Rwandans, as [[Christianity]] is the predominant faith. It is difficult to quantify the number of atheists or agnostics in [[Rwanda]] as they are not officially counted in the census of the country.<ref>{{cite news|title= Is religion losing ground to atheism?|publisher= [[The New Times (Rwanda)]]|date=|url= http://www.newtimes.co.rw/news/index.php?a=69762&i=15458|accessdate=2013-09-16}}</ref>  There is a great stigma attached to being an atheist in Rwanda, even though many people have become atheists in the aftermath of the Rwandan genocide.<ref>{{cite news|title= Rising atheism among Genocide survivors|publisher= [[The New Times (Rwanda)]]|date=|url= http://www.newtimes.co.rw/news/index.php?a=69762&i=15458|accessdate=2013-09-16}}</ref>

