In occultism, '''Pact ink''' is the specially prepared ink that a [[Deal with the Devil|contract with the devil]] must be written in, otherwise the contract is invalid. Various recipes exist. Detailed instructions are rare. The basic recipe is the same as that for [[Iron gall ink]].

==Recipes==

===Pact Ink for Devils and Spirits (14th century)===

*[[Gall|Gall nuts]] - {{convert|10|oz|g}}
*Roman Vitriol or Green Copperas ([[ferrous sulphate]]) - {{convert|3|oz|g}}
*[[alum|Rock alum]] - {{convert|3|oz|g}}
*[[Gum arabic]] - {{convert|3|oz|g}} <ref>{{cite web|url=http://palimpsest.stanford.edu/byform/mailing-lists/bookarts/1999/11/msg00193.html|title=Iron Gall Ink & Permanence|last=Spelker|first=Rich|date=1999-11-19|accessdate=2008-09-19}}</ref>

[[Arthur Edward Waite]]'s ''Book of Black Magic'' gives a similar recipe, but with directions.<ref>{{cite book|last=Waite|first=Arthur Edward|title=The Book of Black Magic: Including the Rites and Mysteries of Goëtic Theurgy, Sorcery, and Infernal Necromancy|publisher=Red Wheel|year=1972|page=161|isbn=0-87728-207-2|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HMrV-BPe5h8C&pg=PA161&lpg=PA161&dq=%22Pact+ink%22&source=web&ots=QogkHG0TkS&sig=tHZ5526MkXQVVdk04Cq1-_TiLoY&hl=en&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=6&ct=result#PPA161,M1}}</ref>

